          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"week_number\":1,\"phase_type\":\"Base\",\"weekly_target_km\":42,\"is_deload_week\":false,\"days\":[{\"day_of_week\":0,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"LongRun\",\"notes\":\"Easy long run at 6:27/km. Build to 16 km this week — a modest step up from your recent 14 km. Keep it conversational the whole way. This is your aerobic foundation work.\"},{\"day_of_week\":1,\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Full rest day. Recovery is where adaptation happens — this is productive training time.\"},{\"day_of_week\":2,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"Easy 8 km at 5:50–6:27/km. Shake out the legs from Sunday. If you feel any IT band tightness, back off and let me know.\"},{\"day_of_week\":3,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Tempo\",\"notes\":\"Tempo session: 2 km warm-up, 4 km at 4:50/km threshold pace, 2 km cool-down (8 km total). This pace should feel comfortably hard — controlled, not all-out.\"},{\"day_of_week\":4,\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Rest or very light movement. Your body is integrating Thursday's quality work. Honor that.\"},{\"day_of_week\":5,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"Easy 8 km at 5:50–6:27/km. Aerobic volume day — keep the effort genuinely easy. No heroics.\"},{\"day_of_week\":6,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"Easy 10 km at 5:50–6:27/km. Capping the week with comfortable aerobic mileage. Finish feeling like you could have done more.\"}],\"week_summary\":\"Welcome to Week 1, Lee. This Base phase week builds gently on your recent 40 km weeks, nudging volume to 42 km while keeping the structure familiar — two easy days bookending a midweek tempo, plus a slightly extended long run. Your VDOT of 42 puts your threshold right at 4:50/km, which matches exactly what you've been hitting in training — a great sign your paces are dialed in. The priority this week is consistency and aerobic volume. Your 1:45 half marathon goal (roughly 4:59/km race pace) is ambitious but very achievable from where you are — it's about a 3-minute PR territory from your current fitness, and we have 16 weeks to build toward it. One thing worth noting: given your IT band history, we'll keep an eye on long run volume increases and make sure hip and glute work stays in your routine. How does this structure feel for your week?\"}"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
